President Biden and First Lady Jill Biden spoke at a meeting on the Cancer Moonshot initiative, which aims to end cancer as we know it and find cures for various types of cancer. The President highlighted the need for a collaborative effort to cut cancer deaths in half and provide support for patients and families. He emphasized the importance of breaking down silos and mobilizing resources across different government departments, including NASA, the Department of Defense, and the Department of Energy. The President also mentioned significant funding secured for cancer research and the signing of laws to help veterans exposed to toxic materials and reduce prescription drug costs for seniors. The First Lady discussed her involvement in the Cancer Moonshot initiative and her focus on improving the patient experience, including the need for patient navigation programs and increased support for them. She highlighted the importance of finding better solutions, treatments, and cures for cancer and urged everyone to join the mission to end cancer.